    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="186"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.248/8–2247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-22T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 22, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1044. For Lovett. Although outstanding instructions prohibit sale US tactical
                    aircraft Argentina, British, Italian, Canadian tactical aircraft being sold
                    here. Representative North American Aviation states Argentina interested
                    purchase 66 overhauled surplus <gloss target="#t_B251">B–25</gloss> bombers. Our
                    unilateral action is ineffective and believe prejudicial US interest. My
                    understanding in Washington was ban had been lifted subject limitations military
                    regulations governing sale aircraft. Please advise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
